  <brief_title>Double Blind Randomized Study Into the Efficacy of Codeine Phosphate Analgesia After Cleft Palate Repair in Infants</brief_title>
  <official_title>Double Blind Randomized Study Into the Efficacy of Codeine Phosphate Analgesia After Cleft Palate Repair in Infants</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Institute of Child Health</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Institute of Child Health</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study examines the analgesic efficacy of codeine phosphate. It is compared to placebo in
      infants receiving morphine after surgery. Codeine may be effective enough to make morphine
      unnecessary.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
